Reactive domain df

Source: R/mod_dfDomains.R
srvr_DomainHash.Rd

Reactive domain df

Usage

srvr_DomainHash(
  rctv_dfDomain,
  strDomainID,
  rctv_dSnapshotDate,
  rctv_strGroupID,
  rctv_strGroupLevel,
  rctv_strSubjectID,
  strCache = NULL
)

Arguments

rctv_dfDomain

reactive dataframe A shiny::reactive() object that returns a domain dataframe.

strDomainID

character The domain data.frame to load.

rctv_dSnapshotDate

reactive Date A shiny::reactive() object that returns the date of a data snapshot.

rctv_strGroupID

reactive character A shiny::reactiveVal() object that returns the GroupID of the selected group (usually site), and can be used to update which group is selected.

rctv_strGroupLevel

reactive character A shiny::reactiveVal() object that returns the selected GroupLevel.

rctv_strSubjectID

reactive character A shiny::reactive() object that returns the SubjectID of the selected participant.

strCache

character An additional string to ensure that a cache key is unique.

Value

A shiny::reactive() that generates a hash of a domain df.
